comment: /**  * Returns the {@link TypeInformation} for the return type of the {@link TableSource}.  * The fields of the return type are mapped to the table schema based on their name.  *  * @return The type of the returned {@code DataSet} or {@code DataStream}.  */
code: /**  * Returns the {@link TypeInformation} for the return type of the {@link TableSource}.  * The fields of the return type are mapped to the table schema based on their name.  *  * @return The type of the returned {@code DataSet} or {@code DataStream}.  */ TypeInformation<T> getReturnType().

comment: /**  * Returns the schema of the produced table.  *  * @return The {@link TableSchema} of the produced table.  */
code: /**  * Returns the schema of the produced table.  *  * @return The {@link TableSchema} of the produced table.  */ TableSchema getTableSchema().

comment: /**  * Describes the table source.  *  * @return A String explaining the {@link TableSource}.  */
code: /**  * Describes the table source.  *  * @return A String explaining the {@link TableSource}.  */ default String explainSource() {     return TableConnectorUtils.generateRuntimeName(getClass(), getTableSchema().getFieldNames()). }
